ted%20in%20the%20southwest%20region%20and%20after%20some%20investigation%2C%20scientists%20were%20able%20to%20trace%20the%20disease%20back%20to%20infected%20deer%20mice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-you-shouldnt-be-afraid-of-yellowstones-hantavirus-outbreak-2012-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoutbreak%20of%20HPS%20hit%20Yosemite%20National%20Park%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202012.%20Ten%20visitors%20who%20were%20staying%20in%20tent%20camps%20became%20infected%20and%20three%20people%20died.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20an%20outbreak%20of%20HPS%20caused%20by%20another%20strain%20of%20hantavirus%20occurred%20in%20seven%20states%20across%20the%20US%2C%20infecting%2017%20people.%20There%20have%20also%20been%20reported%20outbreaks%20of%20HPS%20in%20Panama%20and%20in%20several%20countries%20across%20South%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20common%20way%20people%20are%20infected%20with%20HPS%20is%20when%20they%20breathe%20in%20particles%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhow-to-get-rid-of-mice%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewaste%20left%20by%20infected%20mice%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20fresh%20rodent%20urine%2C%20droppings%2C%20or%20nesting%20materials%20are%20stirred%20up%2C%20tiny%20droplets%20containing%20the%20virus%20get%20into%20the%20air%2C%26quot%3B%20Robert%20Leggiadro%2C%20MD%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20biology%20and%20epidemiology%20at%20Villanova%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20also%20get%20infected%20by%20touching%20urine%2C%20saliva%2C%20or%20feces%20from%20mice%20and%20then%20touching%20your%20mouth.%20It%20is%20very%20unlikely%20to%20be%20spread%20from%20person%20to%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHantavirus%20is%20usually%20found%20in%20rural%20areas%20with%20forests%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fillegal-lab-found-full-of-bioengineered-mice-and-infectious-diseases-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efields%20where%20mice%20can%20live%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228d7ae1b4-906f-491c-90dc-d5abb706348f%5C%22%3EHantavirus%20types%20and%20symptoms%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20multiple%20types%20of%20hantavirus%2C%20all%20carried%20by%20mice%2C%20that%20can%20cause%20disease%20in%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20in%20North%20and%20South%20America%20face%20%26quot%3BNew%20World%26quot%3B%20hantavirus%2C%20which%20causes%20HPS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20early%20symptoms%20of%20HPS%20are%20fatigue%2C%20fever%2C%20and%20muscle%20aches%2C%20but%20after%20the%20disease%20progresses%20for%20a%20few%20days%2C%20the%20lungs%20fill%20with%20fluid%2C%20causing%20coughing%20and%20shortness%20of%20breath.%20According%20to%20the%20CDC%2C%20about%2038%25%20of%20people%20who%20get%20HPS%20may%20die%20from%20the%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20hantaviruses%20in%20Europe%20and%20Asia%20are%20known%20as%20%26quot%3BOld%20World%26quot%3B%20hantaviruses%20and%20cause%20a%20condition%20called%20Hemorrhagic%20Fever%20with%20Renal%20Syndrome.%20The%20early%20symptoms%20of%20HFRS%20include%20headaches%2C%20fever%2C%20nausea%2C%20and%20blurred%20vision.%20Later%20on%2C%20patients%20can%20develop%20low%20blood%20pressure%2C%20leaking%20blood%20vessels%2C%20and%20kidney%20failure.%20Depending%20on%20which%20strain%20of%20hantavirus%20causes%20the%20disease%2C%20HFRS%20kills%20between%201%25%20and%2015%25%20of%20people%20who%20get%20infected%2C%20per%20the%20CDC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20general%2C%20you%20can%20only%20get%20infected%20with%20hantavirus%20from%20direct%20contact%20with%20mice%20bodily%20fluids.%20%26quot%3BThe%20hantaviruses%20that%20cause%20human%20illness%20in%20the%20United%20States%20cannot%20be%20transmitted%20from%20one%20person%20to%20another%2C%26quot%3B%20Leggiadro%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOld%20world%20hantavirus%20is%20usually%20spread%20from%20animals%20to%20humans%20and%20is%20only%20transmitted%20between%20people%20in%20very%20rare%20cases.%20One%20exception%20is%20a%20type%20of%20hantavirus%20found%20in%20Chile%20and%20Argentina%2C%20called%20Andes%20virus%20(ANDV)%2C%20which%20has%20been%20claimed%20to%20transfer%20between%20humans%20via%20close%20contact%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC9574657%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Institutes%20of%20Health%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228b43c565-da69-4c55-a394-bca0c2637204%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20get%20treatment%20for%20hantavirus%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20specific%20treatment%20or%20vaccine%20for%20hantavirus%2C%20Leggiadro%20said%2C%20but%20you%20can%20get%20supportive%20medical%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20disease%20is%20caught%20early%2C%20you%20can%20be%20treated%20in%20an%20intensive%20care%20unit%20and%20given%20oxygen.%20However%2C%20if%20you%20wait%20until%20symptoms%20are%20severe%2C%20treatment%20is%20less%20likely%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20to%20prevent%20hantavirus%2C%20you%20should%20avoid%20any%20activity%20that%20could%20put%20you%20in%20contact%20with%20mice%20or%20their%20nests%2C%20Leggiadro%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOpening%20or%20cleaning%20cabins%2C%20sheds%20and%20outbuildings%2C%20including%20barns%2C%20garages%20and%20storage%20facilities%20that%20have%20been%20closed%20during%20the%20winter%20pose%20a%20potential%20risk%20for%20hantavirus%20infection%2C%20especially%20in%20rural%20areas%2C%26quot%3B%20Leggiadro%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20need%20to%20clean%20out%20these%20areas%2C%20always%20wear%20a%20protective%20mask.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20may%20also%20be%20at%20risk%20while%20camping%20in%20areas%20with%20infected%20mice%2C%20Leggiadro%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20important%20step%20to%20prevent%20hantavirus%20either%20in%20a%20campsite%20or%20your%20home%20is%20to%20keep%20food%20locked%20up%20tightly%20and%20use%20mousetraps%20if%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20hantavirus%20is%20a%20serious%20and%20deadly%20virus%2C%20it%20is%20extremely%20rare%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Leggiadro%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20person%20is%20likely%20not%20at%20risk%20for%20hantavirus%2C%20but%20if%20you%20live%20in%20an%20area%20with%20a%20recent%20outbreak%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20take%20steps%20to%20protect%20yourself%20and%20avoid%20exposure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20been%20in%20contact%20with%20rodents%20or%20their%20nests%20and%20develop%20symptoms%20like%20fever%20and%20deep%20muscle%20aches%2C%20seek%20medical%20attention%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20has%20been%20updated.%20It%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20April%202%2C%202020.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmedical-review-board%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ewas%20previously%20medically%20reviewed%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20by%20Dr.%20Tania%20Elliott%2C%20MD%2C%20who%20specializes%20in%20infectious%20diseases%20related%20to%20allergies%20and%20immunology%20for%20internal%20medicine%20at%20NYU%20Langone%20Health.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fconditions-symptoms%2Fwhat-is-hantavirus%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741556743000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e8634d0671de035810af313%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fconditions-symptoms%2Fwhat-is-hantavirus%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Hantavirus%20is%20a%20disease%20carried%20by%20infected%20rats%20that%20can%20pass%20to%20humans%2C%20but%20very%20rarely%20between%20humans.%20Here's%20what%20you%20need%20to%20know.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22