d%20migrants%20have%20to%20find%20their%20own%20places%20to%20stay%20while%20they%20decide%20where%20they%20want%20to%20go%20next.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20passes%20would%20last%20for%20an%20initial%2030%20days%2C%20but%20could%20be%20renewed%2C%20Abrego%20told%20Associated%20Press%20(AP).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20have%20exactly%2030%20days%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20leave%20Panama%2C%20because%20they%20refused%20...%20to%20accept%20help%20from%20the%20International%20Organization%20for%20Migration%20and%20the%20UN%20Refugee%20Agency%20and%20said%20that%20they%20wanted%20to%20do%20it%20themselves%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20on%20Friday%2C%20a%20day%20before%20migrants%20were%20set%20free.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump's%20Immigration%20Crackdown%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20taking%20office%20on%20January%2020%2C%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20administration%20has%20launched%20a%20massive%20crackdown%20against%20illegal%20immigration%20in%20the%20US.%20The%20administration%20sent%20hundreds%20of%20people%2C%20many%20families%20with%20children%2C%20to%20Panama%20and%20Costa%20Rica%20as%20a%20stopover%20while%20authorities%20organise%20a%20way%20to%20send%20them%20back%20to%20their%20countries%20of%20origin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20arrangement%20fuelled%20human%20rights%20concerns%20when%20hundreds%20of%20deportees%20detained%20in%20a%20hotel%20in%20Panama%20City%20held%20up%20notes%20to%20their%20windows%20pleading%20for%20help%20and%20saying%20they%20were%20scared%20to%20return%20to%20their%20own%20countries.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELawyers%20and%20human%20rights%20defenders%20warned%20that%20Panama%20and%20Costa%20Rica%20were%20turning%20into%20%26quot%3Bblack%20holes%26quot%3B%20for%20deportees%2C%20and%20said%20their%20release%20was%20a%20way%20for%20Panamanian%20authorities%20to%20wash%20their%20hands%20of%20the%20deportees%20amid%20mounting%20human%20rights%20criticism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20international%20refugee%20law%2C%20people%20have%20the%20right%20to%20apply%20for%20asylum%20when%20they%20are%20fleeing%20conflict%20or%20persecution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20that%20refused%20to%20return%20home%20were%20later%20sent%20to%20a%20remote%20camp%20near%20Panama's%20border%20with%20Colombia%2C%20where%20they%20spent%20weeks%20in%20poor%20conditions%2C%20were%20stripped%20of%20their%20phones%2C%20unable%20to%20access%20legal%20counsel%20and%20were%20not%20told%20where%20they%20were%20going%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Uncertain%20Futures'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20migrants%20released%20are%20now%20stranded%20in%20Panama%20with%20no%20resources%20or%20support.%20Among%20them%20is%20Hayatullah%20Omagh%2C%20a%2029-year-old%20who%20fled%20Afghanistan%20in%202022%20after%20the%20Taliban%20took%20control%2C%20into%20a%20legal%20limbo%2C%20scrambling%20to%20find%20a%20path%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20AP%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20refugees.%20We%20do%20not%20have%20money.%20We%20cannot%20pay%20for%20a%20hotel%20in%20Panama%20City%2C%20we%20do%20not%20have%20relatives.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can't%20go%20back%20to%20Afghanistan%20under%20any%20circumstances%20...%20It%20is%20under%20the%20control%20of%20the%20Taliban%2C%20and%20they%20want%20to%20kill%20me.%20How%20can%20I%20go%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20Omagh%20lamented.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20atheist%20and%20member%20of%20an%20ethnic%20minority%20group%20in%20Afghanistan%20known%20as%20the%20Hazara%2C%20he%20said%20returning%20home%20under%20the%20rule%20of%20the%20Taliban%20-%20which%20swept%20back%20into%20power%20after%20the%20Biden%20administration%20pulled%20out%20of%20the%20country%20-%20would%20mean%20he%20would%20be%20killed.%20He%20only%20went%20to%20the%20US%20after%20trying%20for%20years%20to%20live%20in%20Pakistan%2C%20Iran%20and%20other%20countries%20but%20being%20denied%20visas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOmagh%20was%20deported%20after%20presenting%20himself%20to%20American%20authorities%20and%20asking%20to%20seek%20asylum%20in%20the%20US%2C%20which%20he%20was%20denied.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20hope%20was%20freedom.%20Just%20freedom%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20didn't%20give%20me%20the%20chance.%20I%20asked%20many%20times%20to%20speak%20to%20an%20asylum%20officer%20and%20they%20told%20me%20no%2C%20no%2C%20no%2C%20no%2C%20no.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAuthorities%20have%20said%20deportees%20will%20have%20the%20option%20of%20extending%20their%20stay%20by%2060%20days%20if%20they%20need%20it%2C%20but%20after%20that%2C%20many%20like%20Omagh%20don't%20know%20what%20they%20will%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHuman%20rights%20groups%20and%20lawyers%20advocating%20for%20the%20migrants%20help%20many%20of%20them%20find%20shelter%20and%20other%20resources%2C%20while%20dozens%20of%20other%20people%20remained%20in%20the%20camp.%20Many%20of%20the%20migrants%20who%20were%20deported%20were%20fleeing%20violence%20and%20repression%20in%20their%20home%20countries%20and%20could%20not%20return%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20them%20was%2027-year-old%20Nikita%20Gaponov%2C%20who%20fled%20Russia%20due%20to%20repression%20for%20being%20part%20of%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%20community.%20According%20to%20him%2C%20he%20was%20detained%20at%20the%20US%20border%2C%20but%20not%20allowed%20to%20make%20an%20asylum%20claim.%20%26quot%3BOnce%20I%20get%20off%20the%20bus%20(of%20freed%20deportees)%2C%20I'll%20be%20sleeping%20on%20the%20ground%20tonight%2C%26quot%3B%20Gaponov%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoor%20Detension%20Conditions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOmagh%20and%20Gaponov%20are%20among%2065%20migrants%20from%20China%2C%20Russia%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20Afghanistan%2C%20Iran%2C%20Nepal%20and%20other%20nations%20who%20was%20set%20free%20after%20spending%20weeks%20detained%20in%20poor%20conditions%20by%20the%20Panamanian%20government%2C%20which%20has%20said%20it%20wants%20to%20work%20with%20the%20Trump%20administration%20%26quot%3Bto%20send%20a%20signal%20of%20deterrence%26quot%3B%20to%20people%20hoping%20to%20migrate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20no%20way%20home%2C%20Omagh%20said%20that%20leaving%20the%20camp%20was%20a%20relief.%20He%20and%20other%20migrants%20who%20spoke%20to%20the%20AP%20detailed%20scarce%20food%2C%20sweltering%20heat%20with%20little%20relief%20and%20aggressive%20Panamanian%20authorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDetailing%20the%20poor%20detention%20conditions%2C%20the%20report%20said%20a%20small%20riot%20broke%20out%20because%20guards%20refused%20to%20give%20a%20migrant%20their%20phone.%20It%20was%20later%20suppressed%20by%20armed%20guards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPanamanian%20authorities%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20denied%20accusations%20about%20camp%20conditions%2C%20but%20blocked%20journalists%20from%20accessing%20the%20camp%20and%20cancelled%20a%20planned%20press%20visit%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20international%20aid%20organizations%20said%20they%20would%20organise%20travel%20to%20a%20third%20country%20for%20people%20who%20didn't%20want%20to%20return%20home%2C%20Panamanian%20authorities%20said%20the%20people%20released%20had%20already%20refused%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOmagh%20said%20he%20was%20told%20in%20the%20camp%20he%20could%20be%20sent%20to%20a%20third%20country%20if%20it%20gives%20people%20from%20Afghanistan%20visas.%20He%20said%20that%20would%20be%20incredibly%20difficult%20because%20few%20nations%20open%20their%20doors%20to%20people%20with%20an%20Afghan%20passport.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20asked%20authorities%20in%20the%20camp%20multiple%20times%20if%20he%20could%20seek%20asylum%20in%20Panama%2C%20and%20said%20he%20was%20told%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe%20do%20not%20accept%20asylum%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Back%20To%20US'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20those%20freed%20are%20turning%20their%20eyes%20north%20once%20again%2C%20saying%20that%20